OL,4,BHeading should be banned in under-14s
OL,5,Bfootball - Lenny Johnrose
OL,6, Football should ban heading for
OL,7, under-14 children, says former player
OL,8, Lenny Johnrose, who was diagnosed with
OL,9, motor neurone disease in March 2017.
OL,11,FNew research says former professional
OL,12,Ffootballers are three and a half times
OL,13,Fmore likely to die of dementia than
OL,14,Fthose in the general population.
OL,16,FFormer midfielder Johnrose says it
OL,17,F"sickens" him that there are no heading
OL,18,Fbans as there are in the United States.
OL,20,FThe Football Association says there is
OL,21,Fno evidence to support a ban.
